What makes the "specialist" qualified to say Miles is dangerous?  What did the specialist do?  What's the specialist's diagnosis?  Anytime your own genius turns against you, you are all done.  Looks like Miles' genius is not under Miles' control.  Looks like Miles is screwed.  If Miles could only remember when an incident happens.  Memory gone = Mind gone.  Anybody that intelligent will know what a liability a high I.Q. can be.  You do not relate to people your own age at all.  The best you can hope for is to make friends with people outside your age group.  So if the parents don't do exactly the right thing the kid gets thrown away.  Never forget: I.Q. is only a measure of POTENTIAL intelligence and NOT INTELLIGENCE AS SUCH!  Do not assume.
